primary.$description: Use as the primary background for the UI (surfaces, secondary buttons, modal messages, etc)

hover.$description: Primary background hover-state color, for example input fields, menu items, dropdown list elements, etc.

primary-solid.$description: Use as background color for tooltips or popovers.

secondary.$description: Use as the secondary background for the UI (secondary buttons, etc)

secondary_hover.$description: Secondary background hover-state color, for example date/time pickers, language pickers, etc.

secondary-solid.$description: Solid background color that can be applied to featured icons.

tertiary.$description: Use as the tertiary background for the UI (toggles background, tertiary buttons, etc)

active.$description: Background for active selections, such as highlighted menu items in dropdowns.

white.$description: Use when background needs to be white regarding the mode.

disabled.$description: Standard background for disabled components, including primary buttons and toggles.

disabled-subtle.$description: A more toned-down alternative for disabled backgrounds, often found in inputs and checkboxes.

brand-primary.$description: Primary brand background color used for for check icons.

brand-solid.$description: Default solid brand background, used for messages, primary buttons and/or toggles.

brand-solid_hover.$description: Hover-state of the solid brand background.

brand-subtle.$description: Subtle brand background that can be applied to featured icons.

brand-subtlest.$description: Use as the primary background for the UI.

success-subtle.$description: Subtle success background that can be applied to featured icons.

error-subtle.$description: Subtle error background that can be applied to featured icons.

error-solid.$description: Solid error background for error-state buttons, and icons.

error-solid_hover.$description: Solid error background for error-state buttons, and icons.

warning-subtle.$description: Subtle wraning background that can be applied to featured icons.

blanket.$description: Background for overlays used in modals.

primary.$description: Use for primary text, such as body, sentence case headers, and buttons.

subtle.$description: Use for subtle text, such as navigation items, input field labels, and all subheadings.

subtlest.$description: Use for subtlest text, such as meta-data, breadcrumbs and helper text.

white.$description: Use for text on solid dark backgrounds, for example text on Primary/Error buttons.

disabled.$description: Used for text in disabled states.

error-on-subtle.$description: Warning text on subtle error backgrounds.

warning-inverse.$description: Ensures contrast in dark mode scenarios.

primary.$description: High-contrast borders applied to key components like input fields, button groups, and checkboxes.

subtle.$description: Medium-contrast borders used as the default for most elements, including file uploaders and cards.

subtlest.$description: Low-contrast option used for subtle dividers and axis lines in bar and line charts.

white.$description: Use when border needs to be white regarding the mode.

disabled.$description: Standard border color for disabled states that pairs with background-disabled.

disabled-subtle.$description: A subtle border color for disabled states that pairs with background-disabled-subtle.

brand.$description: Used for brand-related elements like focused states in input fields.

brand-hover.$description: Used for brand-related elements in hover states like focused states in input fields.

focused.$description: Used for brand-related elements in hover states like focused states in input fields.

error.$description: Default error-state border color, applied in error states for inputs and file uploaders.

default.$description: Default color for hyperlinks. Used for standard, interactive links in text and UI components.

pressed.$description: Active state color for links when clicked or tapped.

visited.$description: Color for links that have been previously visited.

disabled.$description: Color for inactive or unclickable links.

primary.$description: Highest contrast color used for icons and non-text elements that pairs with text-primary.

subtle.$description: Medium contrast color used for icons and non-text elements that pairs with text-subtle.

subtlest.$description: Low contrast color used for icons and non-text elements that pairs with text-subtlest.

white.$description: Icons or non-text elements that are always white regarding the mode.

disabled-subtle.$description: Disabled subtle-state color used for icons.

brand.$description: Brand color for icons and non-text elements.

success.$description: Standard success-state for icons and non-text elements.

error.$description: Standard error-state for icons and non-text elements.

error-on-subtle.$description: Error-state for icons and non-text elements on subtle error backgrounds.

warning.$description: Standard warning-state for icons and non-text elements.

warning_inverse.$description: Standard warning-inverse-state for icons and non-text elements used on warning background.

info.$description: Standard info-state for icons and non-text elements.

rating-heart.$description: Color used for rating system, specifically for heart ratings.

rating-star.$description: Color used for rating system, specifically for star ratings.

rating-emoji.$description: Color used for rating system, specifically for emoji ratings.

rating-empty.$description: Color used for rating system when empty.
